Running command: cat > /workspace/run_tests.sh << 'BASH'
#!/bin/bash
MOD=998244353
python3 - << 'PY'
from subprocess import Popen, PIPE, run
MOD=998244353
cases=[
("Sample1","4\n1 7 2 9\n", "942786334"),
("Sample2","7\n1 10 100 1000 10000 100000 1000000\n","996117877"),
("N1_A1=1","1\n1\n","0"),
("N1_A1=10","1\n10\n", str(pow(10, MOD-2, MOD)) ),
("N2_5_5","2\n5 5\n", str(pow(25, MOD-2, MOD)) ),
]

for name, inp, expected in cases:
    p = Popen(['python3','/workspace/solution.py'], stdin=PIPE, stdout=PIPE, stderr=PIPE, text=True)
    out, err = p.communicate(inp)
    out = out.strip()
    ok = (out==expected)
    print(name+": expected="+expected+" actual="+repr(out)+" => "+("PASS" if ok else "FAIL"))
PY'
BASH
chmod +x /workspace/run_tests.sh
/workspace/run_tests.sh
